				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^{4}$$\end{document} cm−1, between 103 cm−1 and 106 cm−1 and > 5 × 105 cm−1, respectively.83 However, α(λ) had a similar trend to SE, T and transmission and reflectance (T&R) methods when λ ranged from 200 to 1050 nm.10,90,93,112 In 2013, Wang et al.84 investigated the α of 10 μm ultrathin single-crystal Si using the T method, with an uncertainty value of 5–7%. It was found that the measured data was comparable to the best available data and models. Meanwhile, α of intrinsic silicon is calculated using Kramers–Kronig relation,111 where the α and optical parameters of Si were studied under a temperature of 300 K and in the range of 250–1450 nm. The α(λ) at a wavelength of 250 nm is 1.84 × 106 cm−1, while α(λ) at 1450 nm is 3.2 × 10−8 cm−1.Fig. 3
