With regard to InGaSb, Refaat et al.71 highlighted the functionality of InGaSb operating at 2000 nm for optical communication and atmospheric remote sensing application. The α of In0.15Ga0.85Sb, In0.20Ga0.80Sb, and In0.25Ga0.85Sb was calculated using the interpolation method, as presented in Fig. 5c. In the reported result, α is higher at a shorter λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
